  "text": "The assay for committed CFCs, including CFU-GMs, BFU-Es, and multilineage progenitors (CFU-Mix), was carried out as previously described. [CITATION_1] Briefly, 1 to 5 ϫ 10 4 nucleated cells from mobilized blood or leukapheresis were plated in 35-mm Petri dishes in methylcellulose-based medium (HCC-4100; StemCell Technologies, Vancouver, BC, Canada) supplemented with rhSCF (50 ng/mL; StemCell Technologies), rhIL-3 (10 ng/mL; StemCell Technologies), rhG-CSF (10 ng/mL, StemCell Technologies), rhGM-CSF (10 ng/mL, StemCell Technologies), and erythropoietin (rhEpo, 3 U/mL; R&D Systems, Abingdon, United Kingdom). Progenitor cell growth was evaluated after 14 to 18 days of incubation (37°C, 5% CO 2 ) in a humidified atmosphere.",
